Sentencas: Maintaining the original advantages of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells (SSOFCs), the electrochemical performance can be further enhanced by new quasi-symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: In situ exsolved Co-Fe nanoparticles on the Ruddlesden-Popper-type symmetric electrodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Herein, highly active Ruddlesden-Popper oxides Co-doped LaSr3Fe3O10-delta are investigated as possible symmetric electrodes for SSOFCs, and in situ exsolution of Co-Fe nanoparticles can be homogenously observed on the backbone of this catalyst after high temperature hydrogenation.
Titulo: In situ exsolved Co-Fe nanoparticles on the Ruddlesden-Popper-type symmetric electrodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Spin coated gadolinium doped ceria (GDC) buffer layer onto both sides of the YSZ electrolyte is used to avoid the side reaction of YSZ electrolyte and the symmetric electrodes.
Titulo: In situ exsolved Co-Fe nanoparticles on the Ruddlesden-Popper-type symmetric electrodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: LaSr3Fe3O10-delta showed more excellent electrochemical performance with the high maximum power density of 351.4 mW cm(-2) and the electrode polarization resistance of 0.2894 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C. Moreover, no sign of degradation with this SSOFCs during 100 h long-time testing is observed at 700 degrees C, indicating that the LaSr3Fe3O10-delta symmetrical electrode exhibits good redox reversibility.
Titulo: In situ exsolved Co-Fe nanoparticles on the Ruddlesden-Popper-type symmetric electrodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The high stability and catalytic activity of Ruddlesden-Popper oxides can provide more promise related applications for SSOFCs.
Titulo: In situ exsolved Co-Fe nanoparticles on the Ruddlesden-Popper-type symmetric electrodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
